A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Albania]] on 7 November 1994.<ref name=NS>{{Cite book |title= Elections in Europe: A data handbook |last1= Nohlen |first1= Dieter |authorlink= Dieter Nohlen |last2= Stöver |first2= Philip |date= 31 May 2010 |publisher= Nomos Verlagsgesellschaft |page= 133 |isbn= 978-3-8329-5609-7 }}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of the new constitution published on 6 October,<ref name=NS1>Nohlen & Stöver, p137</ref> which would have given more power to the country's President.<ref>[http://www.setimes.com/cocoon/setimes/xhtml/en_GB/infoCountryPage/setimes/resource_centre/bios/berisha_sali?country=Albania Sali Berisha] SET Times</ref> However, it was rejected by voters,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.princeton.edu/~pcwcr/reports/albania1998.html |title=Albania 1998 |access-date=2011-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404203618/http://www.princeton.edu/~pcwcr/reports/albania1998.html |archive-date=2012-04-04 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> with just 43.6% in favour.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=al011994 Albanien, 6. November 1994 : Verfassung] Direct Democracy</ref> Voter turnout was 84.4%.<ref name=DD/>
